<font color="#FF0000">COMING HOME IN 1967 AND 1986</font><br>
<tt>Sat Feb 15 19:21:21 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I hope to add to the stories of Vietnam, as a girl waiting<br>
for a loved one to come back home from Nam in 1967.  My story is as <br>
heart twisting as the experiences of the soldiers who risked<br>
their lives and came home to a nation that never really welcomed<br>
them back, but it is a story that shows how much this war affected<br>
our whole generation.  It is probably not too different<br>
from the experiences that many women have to tell.<br>
For a time I was involved with the Illinois, Berwyn-Cicero<br>
VietNow organization in Illinois, and was privileged to be a <br>
part of the Welcome Home parade in Chicago,1986 - something <br>
that moved me deeply and will always remember. It would be nice to hear from<br>
anyone who participated.<br>
In any case, thank you for maintaining this web site - and thanks to<br>
the veterans who are willing to join and reach out in<br>
courage with their experiences, however painful they may be.<br>
This web site is a wonderful idea, and I hope we all remain<br>
in dialog with each other. LEST WE FORGET.
<p><code>-- msulli4981@aol.com  (Mary Ann Castaldo) </code><p>


